<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-25T09:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-25T09:30:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/4–2151: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-25T20:00:00+05:30">April
                                        25, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1000. In two conversations today with Ikramullah and one with Dr.
                                Mahmud Husain, Min of States and Frontier Regions who is acting for
                                Prime Minister, it was agreed that text of <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>’s reply to our approach as contained in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 676, Apr 23 shld be
                                telegraphed to Prime Minister now in Peshwar this week. Mahmud
                                Husain is recommending to Prime Minister acceptance of textual
                                language. As soon as reply has been recd Ikramullah promises to
                                inform me immed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>